OL,3,CEpstein files: Survivors say UK
OL,4,C'setting the standard' with
OL,5,Cinvestigations
OL,7,FLiz Stein, who was approached by
OL,8,FGhislaine Maxwell when she was 21,
OL,9,Fsaid people in authority "need to be
OL,10,Ftransparent about what they saw and
OL,11,Fwhat they know".
OL,13,F"At the very base, we know that they
OL,14,Fsaw things and that they know things.
OL,15,FNobody should be above the law, and
OL,16,Fanyone else in this situation would be
OL,17,Fbrought in, questioned, and made to
OL,18,Ftalk about and testify about what they
OL,19,Fsaw."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1773331878
OL,3,CEpstein files: Survivors say UK
OL,4,C'setting the standard' with
OL,5,Cinvestigations
OL,7,F"We are definitely frustrated by a
OL,8,Flack of any motivation to really seek
OL,9,Fjustice in this case. I think that
OL,10,Fwe're seeing a lot of fanfare in the
OL,11,Frelease of these files... Our
OL,12,Fgovernment keeps telling us basically
OL,13,F'there's nothing to see here' and
OL,14,Fthat's just not true.
OL,16,F"Every piece of information I've seen
OL,17,Fin the files has some sort of
OL,18,Finvestigative lead. So we really don't
OL,19,Funderstand why they're not following
OL,20,Fthose leads."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
